sql:
SELECT trend_description
FROM trends_analysis
WHERE confidence_level > 0.9;

SELECT resource_type, available, total
FROM resource_tracking
WHERE region_id = 1;

SELECT MAX(report_date) AS most_recent_report_date
  FROM outbreak_reports
  WHERE region_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- 'hotspots' refers to regions with high average positive rates;
- 'crossed the 1000-vaccination mark' means having more than 1000 total vaccinations administered (vd.total_vaccinations > 1000);
- 'fever' refers to the positive rate of test results (dr.positive_rate);
- An average "fever" of more than 5% means the average positive rate is greater than 0.05 (HAVING AVG(dr.positive_rate) > 0.05).
